A weathered elderly woman's hands resting peacefully on a worn wooden kitchen table, beside a traditional cast iron wok and fresh whole fish on banana leaves, warm golden afternoon light streaming through a window with tropical foliage visible outside, steam rising gently from a cup of tea, the scene rendered in Studio Ghibli's signature soft watercolor style with luminous colors and gentle brushwork, evoking nostalgia and the quiet dignity of a life fully lived, Malaysian kampung kitchen setting blending with hints of modern Singapore visible through the window in the distance, peaceful and bittersweet atmosphere
